One of China’s top pig farming companies imported 900 breeding pigs from Denmark this week, China’s customs said on Wednesday, in the first import of live pigs in a year. <img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-1269051" src="https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Pigs.jpg?resize=300%2C200&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="300" height="200" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Pigs.jpg?resize=300%2C200&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Pigs.jpg?resize=768%2C512&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Pigs.jpg?resize=1024%2C682&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Pigs.jpg?resize=58%2C39&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Pigs.jpg?resize=260%2C173&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Pigs.jpg?resize=195%2C130&amp;ssl=1 195w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Pigs.jpg?resize=115%2C77&amp;ssl=1 115w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Pigs.jpg?resize=560%2C373&amp;ssl=1 560w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Pigs.jpg?w=1280&amp;ssl=1 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> The animals bought by C.P. Pokphand Co, China’s fifth-largest pig producer, arrived on a charter flight in August and spent over a month in quarantine in Xiangyang city in central Hubei province, according to a report on the website of China’s General Administration of Customs, according to Reuters report. It is the first import of live breeding stock since African swine fever began spreading through China’s hog herd over a year ago, reducing demand for breeding animals as farmers tried to fight off the deadly, contagious disease and making quarantine of imported pigs more complicated. But with the disease estimated to have reduced the world’s largest hog herd by more than half, many producers are now speeding up expansion, building new farms and restocking previously infected ones. CP chief executive Bai Shanlin told Reuters last month it plans to raise 10 million pigs a year by 2021, up from 4 million currently. ⤕Why Buhari did not assent to PIGB – Malami ⤕Senate passes redrafted PIG Bill for Buhari’s assent Only a handful of countries are permitted to export live swine to China, which has at times imported up to 10,000 pigs a year for genetic improvement of its herd. The customs database shows imports of breeding pigs from Denmark in August were worth 20.9 million yuan ($2.94 million). The livestock was supplied by DanBred, which is majority-owned by SEGES, the research arm of the Danish Agriculture and Food Council. The company declined to comment on the value of the deal. Vanguard News Nigeria. An outbreak of African swine fever in China is proving to be a windfall for chicken farmers, helping drive up prices of the country’s second-most popular meat to two-and-a-half year highs. September 17, 2018 In "Agric" China’s northern region of Inner Mongolia has reported a new outbreak of African swine fever, the agriculture ministry said on Monday, as authorities struggle to contain the highly contagious diseas September 24, 2018 In "Health" THE Nigerian Agricultural Quarantine Service, NAQS, yesterday, issued a red alert over outbreak of Foot and Mouth Disease, FMD, in Vhembe and Capricorn Districts in Limpopo of South Africa. January 25, 2019 In "Agric"